{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"65217d8c-c228-4f9a-960a-a6febfbc8ab9","content":"The template has the core required fields but has a few gaps before it's NuGet-ready:\n\n**✅ Present & correct:** `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `sourceName`, `author`, `classifications`, `tags`, `symbols`\n\n**❌ Missing — should fix:**\n\n| Field | Why it matters |\n|---|---|\n| `$schema` | Enables editor validation; use `\"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` |\n| `description` | **Critical** — shown in `dotnet new list` and NuGet search. Without it, users can't tell what the template does. |\n| `groupIdentity` | Strongly recommended for NuGet template packs (e.g. `\"MyCompany.WebApi\"`) — groups related templates together. |\n\n**⚠️ Minor considerations:**\n- `preferNameDirectory: true` is a nice-to-have for typical project templates.\n- The `Framework` symbol looks good, but `defaultValue: \"net9.0\"` should match the project file's `<TargetFramework>` placeholder.\n\n**Verdict:** Not ready yet — at minimum add a `description` before publishing.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"764e0267-0f62-4319-89cf-2292109ee251","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I need to check for required and recommended fields.\n\nKey issues I see:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Not strictly required, but highly recommended for validation and editor support.\n2. **Missing `generatorVersions`** or `precedence`** — Not critical but useful.\n3. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** — Nice to have.\n4. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet template packs, especially when you have multiple related templates.\n5. **Missing `description`** — This is important! Without it, `dotnet new list` shows nothing useful.\n\n\n6. **Missing `description`** — This is the critical blocker for NuGet discoverability. The core required fields like `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author`, `classifications`, and `tags` are all present, and `sourceName` handles renaming properly, but without a description the template won't be discoverable to users.\n\n7. **`groupIdentity` for template packs** — This is strongly recommended if this is part of a NuGet template pack, so I should flag that as well.\n\nLet me put together a focused review of what needs to be addressed.","outputTokens":624,"requestId":"A80F:2D915E:C4ED60:E0772E:6A027AF7"},"id":"c57a8651-6fee-4584-886d-c1b36a060755","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:57:41.606Z","parentId":"9ca9b644-f026-4aeb-8ad9-30772d75f61a"}
